Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Quarter @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
onion and a pinch of @salt{}; cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly
softened and lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @ground beef{10%ounce} and @southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}. Cook, breaking
up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

> Pat chicken dry with paper towels. Cook through this step as instructed,
> swapping in chicken (no need to break up into pieces!) or beef for pork.

While pork cooks, in a #large bowl{}, combine @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce},
@mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, half the cilantro, juice from half the lemon (whole lemon
for 4 servings), @sugar{1%tsp}, and a pinch of salt and @pepper{}.

Stir @Tex-Mex paste{1} into pan with pork mixture until fully coated. Taste and
season with salt and pepper. Remove pan from heat.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and
pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with pork filling, @Monterey Jack
cheese{1/4%cup}, slaw, @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, and remaining cilantro. Serve with
any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.